issue.title: Migrate stack to nodejs
issue.body:
I think actually our entire stack can be migrated to nodejs...
It's basically:
.MP3 -> .wav (can be done w/ https://www.npmjs.com/package/sox)
.wav -> .raw (can also likely be done w/ sox)
.raw -> .png (can hopefully be done with jimp - https://www.npmjs.com/package/jimp)
transformations (node-png - https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-png)
and then back up... what are your thoughts? Would definitely make it faster, a lot quicker to stand up, and better integrated!

issue.title: Superimpose a photo on top of a raw img
issue.body: If there's time, steganography would be a good feature to add without too much difficulty. Possible implementation: change the lower order byte (to change color) for every four bytes. User would upload img, python would superimpose, compute result and return to user. If Photoshop can do it so can we.

issue.title: Create a sampled profile for raw songs with a quadtree/similar structure
issue.body:
Create a smaller "signature" or profile pic for a song by sampling, can be done in log(n) time:

algo: "Quadtree [the song image], average the four quadrants as you recurse back up to some predefined level. Treat the array of samples as a 2d array of pixels. You could also tune in how precise you want to be by tuning in how many levels of averaging you want to do. And you can just do math with the indices to partition"
